When creating a base be sure to include a favicon to prevent favicon errors. This fixed "ValueError: Field 'id' expected a number but got 'favicon.ico'"

Use model managers , ie "ModelClass.objects..." to access objects and their attributes/methods

When setting up or using any for of email interaction be sure to reference email information guides found in info.txt.

To fix issues that come from url passing desired object instead of pk ..ie "ValueError: Field 'id' expected a number but got 'JackSmack'." modify the model field that is being refernced by the view and/or url via enhancement
    to_field="".